## Steps

### step 1
id: open-denial-for-writeoff
instruction: Open the denial you want to write off. The encounter detail page shows the denial card with action buttons.
success_criteria: The denial card is visible with action buttons including "Write Off," "Appeal," and "Correct."
anchor: "Write Off"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Use the review-denial flow to navigate to the denial first.

### step 2
id: click-writeoff
instruction: Click the "Write Off" button on the denial card.
success_criteria: A confirmation dialog has appeared asking you to confirm and optionally select a write-off reason.
anchor: "Write Off"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The "Write Off" button is one of the action buttons on the denial card.

### step 3
id: confirm-writeoff
instruction: Select a write-off reason if prompted (e.g., "Patient responsibility," "Payer final decision"), then click "Confirm."
success_criteria: The denial status has changed to "Written Off." If all denials on the encounter are resolved, the encounter closes automatically.
anchor: "Confirm"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Click the confirmation button in the dialog. If a reason dropdown appears, select the most appropriate reason.

## Completion Message
written off. the balance is closed and the encounter will close once all its denials are resolved. the write-off is recorded for accounting and audit purposes.

